  <span id="freeText15859197457414913638" style="display:none">Popsugar Challenge 2021 - A book that has won the Women's Prize for fiction <br /><br />I really didn't think this would make me cry but the words on the last page! The last image in my head! I'm sobbing. <br /><br />Four characters, four back stories, four perspectives.  <br /><br />Gilbert is drafted from Jamaica to help fight Hitler for the motherland. Bernard is drafted from London to India to fight the Japanese. <br /><br />Queenie and Hortense are both reluctant wives and the backbone of this story. Two women, both from small islands who collide in Earls Court. There's only a matter of weeks between the first page and the last but so much happens. <br /><br />This is my first book that features the Windrush Generation and it was uncomfortable on many levels. There is so much I didn't know about Windrush but what really got me was much much loyalty the Jamaicans had to the British whereas the British had no idea where Jamaica was. The motherland called, they volunteered their lives to help. Then after we shoved their help back in their faces. <br /><br />These characters and this plot will stay with me, its so impacting and I learnt so much here. I will definitely be looking up the TV adaptation. <br /><br />I went into this book totally blind and I'm so glad I did. A brilliant read for fans of historical fiction. </span>
